<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:lang="en" xml:id="form-symbolnotmean">
    <teiHeader>
        <fileDesc>
            <titleStmt>
                <title>2.3.4. Symbols (cross, leaf, scroll, fleurette, etc.)</title>
                <respStmt>
                    <resp/>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt>
                <respStmt>
                    <resp/>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt>
            </titleStmt>
            <publicationStmt><p/></publicationStmt>
            <sourceDesc><p/></sourceDesc>
        </fileDesc>
    </teiHeader>
    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="content">
                <div type="leiden">
                <cit type="interpretive">
                    <quote>+, ((cross)), ((+))</quote>
                </cit>
                <cit type="diplomatic">
                    <quote>none</quote>
                </cit>
            </div>
            <div type="explanation">
                <p>Not meaning-bearing symbols, i.e. not to be expanded.</p>
                <p>These symbols should be simply added by typing those supposed to appear in the editorial interpretation; for the diplomatic edition, Atherna Ruby should be used.
                    Alternatively, the symbols can be tagged as follows in the editorial interpretation:
                </p>
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <g ref="#cross"/> = ((cross))
                </egXML>
                <p>or, if a <gi>charDecl</gi> is added to <gi>encodingDesc</gi>:</p>
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <charDecl>
                        <glyph xml:id="cross">
                            <charProp>
                                <localName>glyph-display</localName>
                                <value>+</value>
                            </charProp>
                        </glyph>
                    </charDecl> = ((+))
                </egXML>
            </div>
            </div>
            <div type="responsibility">
                <listBibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <respStmt>
                            <resp>Author</resp>
                            <name>Alessio Sopracasa</name>
                        </respStmt>
                        <respStmt>
                            <resp>Author</resp>
                            <name>Martina Filosa</name>
                        </respStmt>
                    </bibl>
                </listBibl>
            </div>
            <div type="version">
                <p>SigiDoc version: 1.0</p>
            </div>
